{"id": "44164", "title": "Update needed in javadoc for constructor Image(Device, ImageData)", "description": "The javadoc for constructor Image(Device, ImageData) needs to be updated due to a bug. The current javadoc does not mention that an exception is thrown when using certain types of invalid ImageData. Here is an example code snippet that triggers the issue:

import org.eclipse.swt.widgets.*;

public class TestImageInvalidImage {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ImageData data = new ImageData(10, 10, 1, new PaletteData(0xff0000, 0x00ff00, 0x0000ff));
        Image image = new Image(Display.getDefault(), data);
        // image.dispose();
    }
}", "OB": "The javadoc for constructor Image(Device, ImageData) should mention that an exception is thrown if the specified ImageData is invalid.", "EB": "The updated javadoc for constructor Image(Device, ImageData) now includes information about the potential exceptions that can be thrown, specifically when using certain types of invalid ImageData.", "SR": "To recreate this issue, follow these steps:
1. Import org.eclipse.swt.graphics.
2. Use the constructor Image(Device, ImageData) with an invalid ImageData.
3. Observe that an exception is thrown."}
